{{rank|turned|taken|end|241|rather|until|does|Gutenberg}}

===Etymology===
Via Middle English from Old English ''[[hraþor]]''

===Pronunciation===
*(''British'') rä''th'''ə(r), /ˈrɑːðə(r)/, /<tt>"rA:D@(r)</tt>/
*(''American'') ră''th'''ər, /ˈræðər/, /<tt>"r{D@r</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-rather.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æðə(r)|-æðə(r)]]

===Adverb===
'''rather'''

# [[preferably]]
#:Often used with ''[[than]]'', which indicates the less preferable alternative:
#:''I'd '''rather''' stay in all day '''than''' going out with them.''
#:''I'd like this one '''rather than''' the other one.''
# [[quite|Quite]], [[pretty]], [[especially]].
#:''This melon is rather tasteless compared to the one we had last time.''

